<!DOCTYPE html>
	<head>
		<title><%= title %></title>
		<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" />
		<meta name="description" content="<%= description %>" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/style.css">
	</head>
	<body id="<%= current.path %>">
		<%- yield %>
	</body>
	<script type="text/javascript">
		/* Globals for use by the scripts */
		window.chatdomain = "<%= chatdomain %>"
	</script>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="//cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.1/jquery.min.js"></script>
	<script type="text/javascript" src="/chat.js"></script>
	<section>
		<div>
			<small>
			<b>Privacy Policy:</b>
			None of this information is saved. In fact, it is stored in temporary files on the server and is therefore
			removed whenever the server is restarted. They are also removed by a cronjob ran every few hours. If you 
			have trouble please open an issue on the <href="https://github.com/EJEHardenberg/chat-tutorial">github repository</a> describing the problem and I'll try to help. Happy chatting!
			</small>
		</div>
	</section>
</html>
